### Feature A2 attempted: 4-context opcode model → REVERTED

Tried splitting after-match into 3 sub-contexts: after-REP (ctx=0), after-exact (ctx=1),
after-delta (ctx=2). Plus after-literal (ctx=3). Magic: ZXLA → ZXLB.

Result: +1.0 pts regression on all files.
  ntdll.dll:    0.4463 → ~0.4563  (+1.0 pts worse)
  kernel32.dll: 0.4443 → ~0.4543  (+1.0 pts worse)
  user32.dll:   0.3664 → ~0.3764  (+1.0 pts worse)

Root cause: after-REP and after-delta streams too sparse. The 4 extra freq tables
(4×512=2048 bytes) of block header overhead outweighs the modeling gain from
distinguishing REP/exact/delta contexts.

Decision: reverted to ZXLA (2-context model). Magic back to 0x414C585A.

### Feature A3 attempted: 32 literal contexts → REVERTED
Changed N_LIT_CTX 16→32. Result: +6.5 pts regression on all files.
Root cause: 32×512=16KB extra freq tables per 1MB block = 1.56% overhead, dominates all gain.

### Feature A4 attempted: Separate offset streams by size class → REVERTED
Split off_buf into off1_buf (EXACT1/DELTA1), off2_buf (EXACT2/DELTA2), off3_buf (EXACT/DELTA).
Result: neutral to very slightly worse (+0.1–0.4 pts). ZXLB magic.
Root cause: offset byte distributions too similar across size classes. Extra 2 freq tables
(1KB) not justified. Reverted back to ZXLA (0x414C585A).

### Status (end of session)
- [x] Phase 1 / A1: Split param → off_buf + delta_buf streams (−1.1 pts ntdll)
- [~] Phase 1 / A2: 4-context opcode model — TRIED AND REVERTED (+1.0 pts regression)
- [~] Phase 1 / A3: 32 literal contexts — TRIED AND REVERTED (+6.5 pts regression)
- [~] Phase 1 / A4: Separate offset streams by size class — TRIED AND REVERTED (neutral)
- [x] Phase 1 / A5: LRU-5 REP offsets — DONE (−0.1 to −0.3 pts, ZXLB, 2026-04-09)

### Key insight from this session
All A2–A4 failures share the same root cause: block header overhead eats any modeling gain.
The pattern: adding N extra rANS models = N×512 bytes of freq table overhead per block.
At 1MB blocks this overhead is 0.05% per model. A2 added 2 models (+2 pts overhead) → lost.
A3 added 16 models (+16 pts overhead) → big regression. A4 added 2 models → neutral.

To unlock context improvements, need compressed freq tables first (Phase 3 / D1).

A5 (LRU-5 REP) is different: no extra freq tables. Just 2 extra opcodes using 0xF5/0xF6,
cap literal runs at 245 instead of 247. Plan: add TOK_REP3=0xF5, TOK_REP4=0xF6,
expand rep[] array to 5 entries, update DP + trace + decompressor.

